@leewanxian If you want to ensure that a library is installed properly within a Jupyter Kernel, you shouldn't be using the 'bang pip' command `!pip`. You should rather be using the `%pip` magic command to ensure that the library is installed to the current virtual environment (`%pip` will execute a shell command properly while `!pip` is a shell escape command that has a low probability of installing the library to where your Ipython %PATH variable is pointing to)

For further information: 
https://github.com/jupyterlab/jupyterlab-desktop/issues/234#issuecomment-928484514 (this is from Fernando Perez, the creator of Jupyter and IPython)
https://jakevdp.github.io/blog/2017/12/05/installing-python-packages-from-jupyter/ (blog post from Jake VanderPlas, the creator of the `%pip` magic command)
